The paper deals with the analysis of a multiple-input single-output (MISO) broadcast channel (BC) with hybrid channel state information (CSI) for each user. This topic falls under the information theory (cs.IT) and networking and internet architecture (cs.NI) categories. The paper also discusses the Degrees of Freedom (DoF) region, which is a concept in wireless communication and networking, making the sub-categories of signal processing (cs.SI) and multimedia (cs.MM) relevant. Additionally, the paper presents an outer bound for the DoF region, which involves optimization and mathematical modeling, making the category of computational engineering, finance, and science (cs.CE) a possible fit.
